1 - Your volumes will be available in the /home/login/data folder of the
    host machine using Docker. Of course, you have to replace the login
    with yours.

==================================================================================================
2 - To make things simpler, you have to configure your domain name so it points to your
    local IP address.
    This domain name must be login.42.fr. Again, you have to use your own login.
    For example, if your login is wil, wil.42.fr will redirect to the IP address pointing to
    wilâ€™s website.

    ==> solution:
    Linux / macOS:
    Open /etc/hosts with root privileges and add:

    127.0.0.1  alaalalm.42.fr

==================================================================================================

3 - use the Docker secrets to store any confidential information.


